# API Information


main: {
  kit: {
    info: {
      contact: {
        name: "API Support"
        url: "https://www.useragentlookup.com/"
      }
      description: "This API allows users to parse and retrieve information about user agents for free. It has no limitations or rate limiting, enabling unlimited requests by simply calling the appropriate endpoint with the user agent string."
      license: {
        name: "Free to use"
      }
      servers: [
        {
          description: "Production server"
          url: "https://www.useragentlookup.com/api"
        }
      ]
      termsOfService: "https://www.useragentlookup.com/"
      title: "User Agent Lookup API"
      version: "1.0.0"
      tagline: "Parse a User-Agent string into structured browser, OS, and device data"
      homepage: "https://www.useragentlookup.com/"
      docs_url: "https://www.useragentlookup.com/"
      license_short: "Free to use; no API key, no rate limiting"
      license_md: `- Free to use for any number of requests
- No authentication or API key required
- No published rate limits
- CORS is not enabled, so calls must be made server-side`
      about_md: `[User Agent Lookup](https://www.useragentlookup.com/) is a small public service that parses raw \`User-Agent\` strings and returns structured information about the requesting browser, operating system, and device.

What you get from the API:

- A single \`GET\` endpoint that accepts a \`ua\` query parameter containing the User-Agent string
- A JSON response with parsed fields describing the client (the maintainers note the output is stable but new fields may be added over time)

Operational notes:

- Base URL: \`https://www.useragentlookup.com/api\`
- No API key or auth header is required
- The service advertises no rate limiting and high uptime, but CORS is disabled, so requests should be issued from a server rather than directly from a browser`
      entity_desc: {
        user_agent: "A parsed representation of a `User-Agent` header string, retrieved via `GET /user-agent?ua={user-agent-string}`."
      }
      auth: false
    }
  }
}
